cu500_pal | 1 | Carefully executed Qur&apos;anic Maghribi script.  Diacritical points are fully used except those for final f, q, n, and y.  The modern vowel signs are also fully used and, with the shaddahs, are in red.  A yellow and green dot indicate hamzah and waslah respectively.  The alif of prolongation is in red.  Where it follows the lam, the scribe has written it before the lam.  The surah titles and the word hizb are written in ornamental Kufic of fair execution.  The manuscript is well-written.  Scribal errors are few, consisting chiefly of omissions, which have been carefully supplied in the margin by the original scribe.  Reading symbols are lacking, except s for silah or waslah.
