cu590_con | 1 | Fine thin paper.  The 70 original folios were supplemented with 8 new folios at the beginning and 15 new folios at the end, with the first 16 folios interleaved.  The manuscript is in good condition, except for the binding.  Leaves are missing between folios 40-41 and 89-90.  The two leaves have been cut out, leaving only the inner margin, which bears traces of the script.  They belonged to the original manuscript, but since the present text is continuous, they may have been cut out by the original scribe because of some scribal errors.
